%20NPR%20and%20PBS.%20That's%20equivalent%20to%20two%20years%20of%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20%248.3%20billion%20includes%20various%20forms%20of%20foreign%20aid%3A%20%246.3%20billion%20of%20that%20funding%20is%20related%20to%20the%20US%20Agency%20for%20International%20Development%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-dismantling-usaid-could-have-life-threatening-consequences-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUSAID%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20foreign%20aid%20agency%20that%20DOGE%20shuttered%20in%20the%20early%20months%20of%20the%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20includes%20%242.5%20billion%20in%20development%20assistance%2C%20%241.65%20billion%20in%20economic%20support%20funds%2C%20and%20%24900%20billion%20for%20global%20health%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20has%20also%20requested%20that%20Congress%20rescind%20%241.13%20billion%20in%20contributions%20to%20various%20international%20organizations%2C%20including%20%24800%20billion%20for%20migration%20and%20refugee%20assistance%2C%20and%20a%20combined%20%2464%20million%20for%20organizations%20like%20the%20Inter-American%20Foundation%2C%20the%20African%20Development%20Foundation%2C%20at%20the%20United%20States%20Institute%20of%20Peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2216077e04-88bd-42cc-b308-94b3e578374b%5C%22%3EThere's%20a%20limited%20amount%20of%20time%20to%20get%20this%20done%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-impoundment-trump-control-government-congress-spending-plan-doge-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EImpoundment%20Control%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20ICA%2C%20the%20president%20is%20generally%20required%20to%20spend%20money%20that%20Congress%20has%20already%20approved.%20The%20law%20was%20passed%20in%201974%2C%20after%20President%20Richard%20Nixon%20refused%20to%20spend%20money%20on%20a%20variety%20of%20programs%20that%20he%20disagreed%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20and%20his%20allies%20have%20argued%20that%20this%20law%20is%20unconstitutional%2C%20and%20some%20Republicans%20in%20Congress%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frepublicans-trump-impoundment-act-sweeping-power-over-government-spending-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eintroduced%20a%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20eliminate%20it%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20administration%20has%20also%20withheld%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20federal%20funding%20already%2C%20and%20the%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F05%2F22%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Ftrump-federal-funds-gao.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20administration%20is%20violating%20the%20ICA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20ICA%20also%20provides%20for%20the%20president%20to%20make%20rescission%20requests%20to%20Congress%2C%20and%20the%20Trump%20administration%20is%20now%20using%20that%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20law%2C%20Congress%20has%2045%20days%20of%20consecutive%20session%20to%20approve%20the%20cuts%2C%20or%20the%20money%20must%20be%20spent.%20That%20means%20lawmakers%20have%20until%20early%20September%20to%20get%20this%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20other%20bills%2C%20rescission%20bills%20only%20require%20a%20simple%20majority%20in%20the%20Senate%20to%20pass.%20That%20means%20Democrats%2C%20who%20are%20expected%20to%20broadly%20oppose%20the%20legislation%2C%20have%20no%20way%20of%20blocking%20the%20cuts%20on%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20GOP%20support%20will%20be%20unanimous.%20Republican%20Sen.%20Lisa%20Murkowski%20of%20Alaska%2C%20for%20example%2C%20recently%20wrote%20an%20op-ed%20in%20a%20local%20paper%20opposing%20cuts%20to%20public%20broadcasting%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20time%20a%20president%20tried%20to%20do%20this%2C%20it%20failed.%20In%202018%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20asked%20Congress%20to%20rescind%20%2415%20billion%20in%20federal%20spending%2C%20but%20the%20bill%20failed%20to%20pass%20the%20Senate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20the%20full%20text%20of%20the%20White%20House's%20rescission%20request%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Fembed.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25960446-proposed-rescissions-of-budgetary-resources%2F%3Fembed%3D1%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-cuts-npr-pbs-foreign-aid-request-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748988644000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683f566dc19ab3675c1092e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-cuts-npr-pbs-foreign-aid-request-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20foreign%20aid%20and%20public%20broadcasting%20cuts%20could%20be%20the%20first%20of%20several%20%26quot%3Brescission%26quot%3B%20requests%20sent%20to%20Congress%20in%20the%20coming%20months.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bmetzger%40insider.com%20(Bryan%20Metzger)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A297%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-cuts-npr-pbs-foreign-aid-request-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Andor%E2%80%99%20Creator%20Says%20Disney%20Spent%20%E2%80%98%24650%20Million%20for%2024%20Episodes%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98We%20Fought%20Hard%E2%80%99%20for%20Money%20After%20Being%20Told%20in%20Season%202%3A%20%E2%80%98Streaming%20Is%20Dead.%20We%20Don%E2%80%99t%20Have%20the%20Money%20We%20Had%20Before%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748988348000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2FCassian-Andor-finale.png%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22orig