Fwww.brooklinen.com%252Fproducts%252Fdown-pillow%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrooklinen%20Down%20Pillow%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20lying%20down.%20Then%2C%20I%20lay%20my%20face%20on%20the%20pillow%20for%20two%20minutes.%20After%20the%20two-minute%20period%2C%20I%20measured%20again.%20Finally%2C%20I%20measured%20the%20last%20temperature%20two%20minutes%20after%20lying%20down%20to%20determine%20how%20the%20pillowcase%20dissipates%20heat.%20I%20also%20noted%20if%20I%20overheated%20in%20my%20sleep%20during%20the%20testing%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDurability%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20tested%20durability%20by%20scratching%20each%20silk%20pillowcase%20with%20my%20fingernails%2050%20times%20in%20two%20places%3A%20once%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20pillow%20and%20once%20near%20a%20seam.%20This%20test%20was%20meant%20to%20replicate%20accidentally%20scratching%20your%20pillowcase%2C%20pet%20nails%2C%20or%20snagging%20an%20earring%20on%20the%20fabric.%20My%20partner%2C%20who%20has%20stubble%2C%20slept%20with%20each%20silk%20pillowcase%20for%20seven%20nights%20to%20check%20for%20noticeable%20damage%20from%20abrasion.%20I%20also%20looked%20for%20torn%20threads%20and%20pilling%20after%20washing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECare%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20followed%20the%20care%20instructions%20for%20each%20silk%20pillowcase.%20After%20washing%20and%20drying%2C%20I%20also%20checked%20how%20well%20any%20stains%20were%20removed%20from%20the%20pillowcase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b8409ffb-9ad8-47ba-afcf-b281604333d7%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22FAQs%5C%22%3ESilk%20pillowcase%20FAQs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat's%20the%20difference%20between%20silk%20and%20satin%20pillowcases%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESilk%20is%20a%20natural%20animal%20product%2C%20whereas%20satin%20is%20a%20type%20of%20weave%20that%20can%20be%20made%20from%20any%20material.%20Silk%20pillowcases%20are%20generally%20more%20expensive%20than%20satin%20pillowcases%20since%20creating%20and%20harvesting%20silk%20is%20cumbersome.%20Both%20silk%20and%20satin%20pillowcases%20are%20good%20for%20hair%20and%20skin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20is%20%26quot%3Bmomme%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20why%20does%20it%20matter%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20momme%20refers%20to%20the%20weight%20of%20silk%2C%20so%20a%20heavier%20weight%20means%20there%20are%20more%20silk%20fibers%20in%20the%20fabric%2C%20according%20to%20Walker.%20%26quot%3BMomme%26quot%3B%20(pronounced%20%26quot%3Bmummy%26quot%3B)%20is%20a%20historic%20unit%20of%20weight%20measurement.%20The%20abbreviation%20is%20%26quot%3Bmm%26quot%3B%20which%20should%20not%20be%20confused%20with%20millimeter%2C%20which%20is%20a%20measurement%20of%20thickness%20or%20length%20%E2%80%94%20when%20you%20see%20%26quot%3Bmm%26quot%3B%20in%20reference%20to%20silk%20it%20is%20a%20measurement%20of%20weight%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAlthough%20we%20now%20have%20much%20more%20common%20units%20of%20measurement%20for%20weight%2C%20momme%20is%20still%20used%20in%20the%20silk%20trade.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSilk%20is%20sold%20by%20weight%20and%20always%20has%20been%20sold%20this%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Walker%20continued.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20comparing%20fabrics%20of%20the%20same%20weave%20structure%20(silk%20charmeuse%2C%20a%20crepe-back%20satin%2C%20for%20instance)%2C%20the%20heavier%20momme%20indicates%20a%20thicker%20yarn%20and%20generally%20a%20higher%20quality%20fabric.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EIs%20mulberry%20silk%20better%20than%20other%20types%20of%20silk%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Walker%20said%2C%20mulberry%20silk%20is%20made%20by%20feeding%20the%20Bombyx%20mori%20silk%20moth%20caterpillar%20mulberry%20leaves.%20%26quot%3BOther%20breeds%20of%20silk-producing%20moths'%20caterpillars%20eat%20a%20wider%20variety%20of%20leaves%2C%20which%20permanently%20color%20the%20silk%2C%26quot%3B%20Walker%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20what%20you%20eat!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20the%20creation%20process%2C%20Walker%20also%20says%20that%20mulberry%20silk%20is%20generally%20better%20than%20other%20types%20of%20silk.%20%26quot%3B'Mulberry%20silk'%20is%20arguably%20of%20higher%20quality%20than%20many%20other%20types%20of%20silk%20due%20to%20its%20consistent%20fiber%20diameter%20and%20its%20ease%20of%20dyeing%20into%20vibrant%20colors%2C%26quot%3B%20Walker%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20do%20I%20clean%20a%20silk%20pillowcase%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWalker%20recommends%20handwashing%20your%20silk%20pillowcase%20and%20air%20drying%20it%2C%20rather%20than%20putting%20it%20in%20the%20dryer.%20%26quot%3BTo%20ensure%20the%20longest%20life%20for%20your%20silk%20pillowcase%2C%20it%20is%20recommended%20to%20hand%20wash%20it%20with%20mild%20soap%20or%20detergent%2C%20roll%20in%20a%20towel%20to%20remove%20the%20excess%20water%2C%20and%20lay%20flat%20to%20dry.%20A%20light%20rinse%20in%20a%20liquid%20fabric%20softener%20can%20help%20preserve%20the%20softness%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Be%20gentle%20with%20the%20silk%20when%20washing%2C%20as%20it%20is%20weaker%20when%20wet.%20Dry%20cleaning%20is%20also%20an%20excellent%20option.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDo%20silk%20pillowcases%20help%20with%20frizz%20and%20wrinkles%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Jaliman%20said%20that%20silk%20pillowcases%20help%20with%20wrinkles%20and%20skin%20texture.%20%26quot%3BSilk%20reduces%20friction%20on%20the%20skin%2C%20so%20it%20helps%20prevent%20sleep%20lines%20and%20wrinkles%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSilk%20absorbs%20less%20moisture%20than%2C%20for%20example%2C%20cotton%2C%20so%20it's%20better%20for%20keeping%20your%20products%20on%20the%20skin%20and%20not%20absorbing%20them%20into%20the%20pillowcase.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESilk%20pillowcases%20also%20work%20to%20combat%20frizz.%20%26quot%3BSince%20silk%20is%20very%20smooth%2C%20it%20reduces%20friction%20and%20prevents%20frizziness%20of%20the%20hair%2C%26quot%3B%20Jaliman%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20also%20helps%20to%20maintain%20a%20hairstyle%20longer%20because%20of%20less